HEADWORD: Postmaster-general
<hw>Post"mas`ter-gen"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Postmasters-general</plw>.</plu> <def>The chief
officer of the post-office department of a government. In the United
States the postmaster-general is a member of the cabinet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

